.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-SWEEP\-RESULTS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.49" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-sweep\-results \- Tabulate per\-trial results for one sweep
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose sweep results [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read a persisted sweep manifest and print one tidy row per trial (each sweep variable as its own column, status, and parsed objective) as text, JSON, or CSV. Read\-only: unlike `sweep observe`, it never writes objective state back to the manifest.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--sweep\-id\fR \fIID\fR
Sweep id to tabulate; defaults to the latest sweep.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json, csv.
.TP
\fB--include\fR \fIMETRIC\fR
Extra per\-trial columns: score, energy (comma\-separated).
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--sstat\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sstat executable. Default: sstat.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose sweep submit \-f train.yaml \-\-dry\-run
hpc\-compose sweep submit \-f train.yaml
hpc\-compose sweep status \-f train.yaml
hpc\-compose sweep list \-f train.yaml
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
hpc\-compose(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep\-list(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep\-observe(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep\-status(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep\-stop(1), hpc\-compose\-sweep\-submit(1)
